10
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:51,030
It's where they pass every day.

11
00:02:51,030 --> 00:02:52,750
How about we put it in his bedroom?

12
00:02:52,750 --> 00:02:54,110
It's vacant, anyway.

13
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:58,190
It should be put somewhere lively.

14
00:03:01,030 --> 00:03:01,800
Mr. Wang.

15
00:03:04,190 --> 00:03:05,000
Are you OK?

16
00:03:06,550 --> 00:03:07,320
Yes.

17
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:10,080
Mr. Wang, our team members
have all come.

18
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:12,080
If you need any help, let us know.

19
00:03:12,550 --> 00:03:13,000
OK.

20
00:03:14,270 --> 00:03:15,320
My son loves the pork knuckle

21
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:16,750
I make, you know?

22
00:03:16,750 --> 00:03:18,270
He used to think
we had too many vegetables.

23
00:03:18,270 --> 00:03:20,360
Every time I made it, he ate a lot.

24
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:23,270
Where shall I put the portrait?

25
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:24,550
Here.

26
00:03:28,110 --> 00:03:29,520
Somewhere warm.

27
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:33,080
Facing the sun.

28
00:03:50,620 --> 00:03:57,620
(Song Yukun, the factory manager, paid
a caring visit to vigilante Wang Xiang.)

29
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:33,880
Look.

30
00:04:34,830 --> 00:04:36,480
How about I put the portrait here?

31
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:38,950
Is it straightened?

32
00:05:08,830 --> 00:05:10,160
We don't hang a portrait of him.

33
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,640
And don't hang that of me after I die.

34
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:12,880
Meisu, I...

35
00:05:14,670 --> 00:05:15,320
Meisu.

36
00:05:16,830 --> 00:05:17,830
Meisu, are there more chairs?

37
00:05:17,830 --> 00:05:18,790
We still need one.

38
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:22,950
I don't want to see you.

39
00:05:34,350 --> 00:05:35,390
What are you waiting for?

40
00:05:35,390 --> 00:05:36,440
Enjoy the meal. Hurry.

41
00:05:36,440 --> 00:05:36,760
Come on.

42
00:05:36,760 --> 00:05:37,600
Take up your chopsticks.

43
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:39,230
Quanli.

44
