Eat. Not too many fishbones.

65
00:06:56,110 --> 00:06:58,510
Mr. Wang and Ms. Luo,

66
00:06:58,510 --> 00:06:59,670
I came to check up on you.

67
00:07:06,350 --> 00:07:07,350
Come and sit, Captain Ma.

68
00:07:07,350 --> 00:07:09,000
He won't come in. You enjoy the food.

69
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:13,230
Come out with me.

70
00:07:39,350 --> 00:07:40,600
What have you got about Yang's case?

71
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,070
Suicide.

72
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:49,270
He jumped off the
Xiaoliang River Bridge.

73
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:54,230
His body, had no other wounds, but
the bruises of knocking onto the water.

74
00:07:58,790 --> 00:07:59,920
I knew this.

75
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:02,390
Other police officers told me about it.

76
00:08:04,070 --> 00:08:05,070
But that is wrong.

77
00:08:06,950 --> 00:08:07,880
I want to know your deduction.

78
00:08:12,390 --> 00:08:13,070
When I see you like this,

79
00:08:13,070 --> 00:08:14,440
I feel really bad.

80
00:08:15,350 --> 00:08:16,070
But think about it.

81
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:18,760
Does Wang Yang want
to see you like this?

82
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:25,000
If you want me to get better,
find out the truth.

83
00:08:27,550 --> 00:08:30,320
I want to know who killed my son.

84
00:08:31,350 --> 00:08:32,760
Fine, fine.

85
00:08:33,350 --> 00:08:34,000
I'll investigate it.

86
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,080
You're fencing with me.

87
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:38,520
But now, this is the truth.

88
00:08:39,280 --> 00:08:41,710
You should believe the evidence
and the police.

89
00:08:41,710 --> 00:08:43,110
You're a policeman.

90
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:46,640
I trusted you.

91
00:08:48,350 --> 00:08:49,080
And then?

92
00:08:51,910 --> 00:08:52,640
What happened to my son?

93
00:08:55,550 --> 00:08:57,960
If you had told me what you had known...

94
00:08:57,960 --> 00:08:59,440
I called you.

95
00:09:00,910 --> 00:09:02,000
Did you reply?

96
00:09:15,790 --> 00:09:17,110
This isn't what I want.

97
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:19,640
I want my son back.

98
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:24,030
He didn't kill anyone.

99
00:09:25,550 --> 00:09:27,000
He couldn't have killed himself, either.

100
00:09:29,790 --> 00:09:30,320
Leave.

101
00:09:41,470 --> 00:09:41,910
Well done,

102
00:09:41,910 --> 00:09:42,400
Qun.

103
00:09:43,150 --> 00:09:44,710
You've solved such a big case.

104
00:09:44,710 --> 00:09:45,640
Stop calling him Qun.

105
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:47,350
Call him Captain Li.

106
00:09:47,350 --> 00:09:48,520
Don't wait.

107
00:09:48,520 --> 00:09:50,000
Call me Captain Li now.

108
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:51,470
Captain Li is getting excited.

109
00:09:51,470 --> 00:09:52,760
Come on. Get Captain Li some water.

110
00:09:52,760 --> 00:09:53,760
Fine, fine.

111
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:55,590
I just helped our colleagues.

112
00:09:55,590 --> 00:09:56,790
Give me some help, too.

113
00:09:56,790 --> 00:09:57,520
OK.

114
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:25,230
No more water, don't you know?

115
00:10:27,670 --> 00:10:29,030
What are you thinking all day long?

116
00:10:29,710 --> 00:10:30,640
Darn it!

117
00:10:58,550 --> 00:10:59,670
Didn't you quit smoking?

118
00:11:00,350 --> 00:11:01,440
Get me the file.

119
00:11:18,320 --> 00:11:18,910
But Captain Ma,

120
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:21,590
Director Zhu said

121
00:11:21,590 --> 00:11:23,400
I would do the follow-up on this case.

122
00:11:24,030 --> 00:11:25,110
And you'll have a couple of days off.

123
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:26,640
What do you mean?

124
00:11:27,670 --> 00:11:28,760
Get over me with him?

125
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:30,910
No. I don't mean that.

126
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,670
Even if you do, hold it back.

127
00:11:36,790 --> 00:11:38,440
Want a revolt, Captain Li?

128
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:41,000
I can't order you about, huh?

129
00:11:44,230 --> 00:11:45,880
Didn't you hear me?

130
00:11:45,880 --> 00:11:47,400
What did I say?

131
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:48,790
Get me the file!

132
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:14,200
What about your self-criticism?

133
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:15,670
No time for that.

134
00:12:17,030 --> 00:12:18,710
What you did in Songhe got messier.

135
00:12:18,790 --> 00:12:20,520
Illegal interrogation and fight.

136
00:12:20,530 --> 00:12:22,200
You'll certainly be disciplined.

137
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:24,470
Go write a self-criticism
and stop working.

138
00:12:24,470 --> 00:12:25,880
When you can be reinstated
will be decided later.

139
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:26,880
Then how could I investigate the case?

140
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:28,000
Don't bother!

141
00:12:28,550 --> 00:12:29,710
It's no longer your concern!

142
00:12:29,710 --> 00:12:31,150
Someone else will investigate it.

143
00:12:31,150 --> 00:12:32,110
Li Qun?

144
00:12:32,110 --> 00:12:33,320
I disapprove!

145
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:35,080
You have no right to disapprove!

146
00:12:35,790 --> 00:12:37,400
Go work on your self-criticism.

147
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:39,030
I'll investigate Weijun!

148
00:12:39,030 --> 00:12:40,150
Immediately!

149
00:12:41,550 --> 00:12:43,550
Ma Desheng, are you out of your mind?

150
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:46,110
Do you know how Lu Wenzhong was killed?

151
00:12:46,470 --> 00:12:50,150
Song Yukun embezzled his workers'
resettlement money and has been arrested!

152
00:12:50,150 --> 00:12:51,550
Have you ever asked about these cases?

153
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:53,000
Go look in the mirror.

154
00:12:53,230 --> 00:12:55,670
Do you still look like a policeman?

155
00:12:56,470 --> 00:12:58,030
And can you still recognize yourself?

156
00:13:34,910 --> 00:13:36,150
What are you doing, Ma Desheng?

157
00:13:46,640 --> 00:13:47,880
Are you insane?

158
00:14:00,710 --> 00:14:02,110
I don't deserve this uniform.

159
00:14:02,640 --> 00:14:03,400
I'll quit.

160
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:08,350
Come back!

161
00:14:24,350 --> 00:14:26,200
Thank you for coming.

162
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,350
Thank you.

163
00:14:27,350 --> 00:14:28,520
We should go, Mr. Wang.

164
00:14:28,520 --> 00:14:29,000
OK.

165
00:14:29,470 --> 00:14:30,320
You go first.

166
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:31,670
I'll have a word with Mr. Wang.

167
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:38,840
Mr. Wang.

168
00:14:40,910 --> 00:14:41,840
I... I just...

169
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:42,550
I...

170
00:14:42,550 --> 00:14:44,110
We can't really help much.

171
00:14:44,110 --> 00:14:45,520
This is all we can give.

172
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:46,350
Please take it.

173
00:14:46,350 --> 00:14:48,110
My problem has been solved.

174
00:14:48,110 --> 00:14:49,790
When my leg recovers,
I'll be back for work.

175
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:51,280
Not too much money. Just take it.

176
00:14:53,550 --> 00:14:54,400
Mr. Wang, what are you doing?

177
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:56,230
You need more money than me.

178
00:14:56,230 --> 00:14:57,150
You have a son to raise.

179
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:01,400
But in my family,
only my wife and I live.

180
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:02,350
We don't need a lot of money.

181
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:05,440
Quanli.

182
00:15:07,710 --> 00:15:11,080
Whatever happens, bring your son up.

183
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:13,150
It's what a man should do.

184
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:16,550
This is where we part.

185
00:16:00,710 --> 00:16:01,520
Meisu?

186
00:16:06,640 --> 00:16:07,350
Meisu?

187
